snippet.textDisplay: I believe that the reason the aluminum foil sparks is because, as it's crinkled up, the gaps between the ridges are just the right distance apart to create an arc. That's why, after a while, it stops sparking, because all of the arc points have melted and grown too far apart for the spark to occur.
snippet.textOriginal: I believe that the reason the aluminum foil sparks is because, as it's crinkled up, the gaps between the ridges are just the right distance apart to create an arc.
